Both pieces of the graph of $y=k(x)$ have slope $\pm 2$, so the total length of this graph along the interval $-3.5\le x\le 3.5$ is $\sqrt{7^2+(2\cdot 7)^2} = \sqrt{245}$. Therefore, $\ell^2=\boxed{245}$.

